spanGrp.span: ‘I saw that a mouse was cooking;
Yís të í (m) sũã'-ra koño kalu uliwã
he put something into the pot.
Others called him and he replied.
He went to fetch his clothes, took a shower and left.
Í mẽnẽ í sua yulö Í jugáu-mĩ í mẽnẽu-mĩ
The other one came to pick him up. He got in and left;
e-gla deũ jie yulö karro Í jẽk jia-ká mẽnẽu
they went far and then they got hurt;
í shkáu-mĩ komĩ' Jeska jeska í shkanã' jela
the owner ended up on a branch.
A car came by and took him to the doctor to be given medicine.
Jeska (_) karro deu-nẽ-wã í mẽnẽtse-mĩ doktor sã (m) sũã'-glö (m) pepli mõ-glö ĩã
The frog helped him. He brought him back.
Deu (_) jeska bulbi deu-te í kimã' betetse í wã
so he [the frog] put him on a bed, fed him and covered him with a blanket.
Mãga-ite jaka inga Chewã-ite kitiá-wã-ite kobija wa
He saw how he got cured.
when they were going on the road, the mouse was coming to pick them up;
Í damĩu ñala wara koño dajũ-te-nẽ í tsõ
Je të í jiá-ka karro nã mẽnẽtse-mĩ
